Comparable Interface

1. Present in java.lang package

2. Contains only one method
		public int compareTo(Object obj)
		
3. Meant for Default Natural Sorting order

# for default natural sorting order

---------------------------------------------

Comparator Interface

1. Present in java.util package
2. Contains two methods: 
			public int compare(Object obj1, Object obj2)
			public boolean equals(Object obj)
# for customized sorting

Methods:
		
public int compare(Object obj1, Object obj2)	
-You can give your own implementations to this method

public boolean equals(Object obj)
-You do not need to provide implementation for this method in the implementing classes
(because it is present in Object class as well)

